 From the new cases, 406 are Kenyans while 21 are foreigners. The number of Covid-19 cases in Kenya have increased to 95,195 after 427 more people tested positive for the virus in the last 24 hours.
The cumulative tests are now 1,021,880. From the new cases, Health Cabinet Secretary Mutahi Kagwe said 406 are Kenyans while 21 are foreigners.
In terms of gender distribution, Mr Kagwe said 256 are male while 171 are female. The youngest case is five years old while the oldest is aged 87.



