He said that 286 patients recovered, raising total number of those declared free of the virus to 76, 508. Another 228 patients were in home-based care, while 58 were discharged from various hospitals.
Death toll
He said that the death toll in the country had risen to 1,648 after one more patient succumbed to the disease over the past 24 hours.
In terms of distribution per county, the CS said that Nairobi recorded 176 cases, Mombasa (68), Kiambu (58), while Kitui had 14 cases.



