Kilifi recorded 14 cases, Kwale (13) and Kisumu (12). Machakos and Kajiado had 10 cases each while Busia had seven cases, Muranga (6), Bungoma (5), Lamu (5), Taita Taveta (5) and Nandi (3). Meru, Kirinyaga, and Embu counties recorded two cases each. Kakameha, Siaya, Makueni, Nyamira, Mandera and Homa Bay counties recorded one case each.
Currently, there are 789 patients admitted to various health facilities in the country, while 3,705 are on Home Based Isolation and Care.
Mr Kagwe said that 43 patients are in Intensive Care Unit, 20 of whom are on ventilatory support, while another 21 are on supplemental oxygen.
High Dependency Unit
 Another 29 patients are separately on supplementary oxygen. Out of this number, Mr Kagwe said that 24 patients are in the general wards while five are in the High Dependency Unit.



